<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
	<PropertyGroup>
		<Description>The RFC 9457 Problem Details payload for the Cohesion Web pipeline: the ProblemDetails model, an AOT-safe application/problem+json writer built directly on Utf8JsonWriter (no reflection), and the WriteProblemDetailsAsync response extension. The payload library for error responses - how errors are surfaced (the OnError hook) is composed by the application.</Description>
		<!-- Deviates from the repo namespace-matches-assembly rule per design decision:
		     the payload surfaces in Assimalign.Cohesion.Web so the ProblemDetails model
		     avoids a namespace/type collision (Assimalign.Cohesion.Web.ProblemDetails.ProblemDetails)
		     and WriteProblemDetailsAsync is discoverable with the pipeline's using
		     (matches the Assimalign.Cohesion.Http feature-package precedent). -->
		<RootNamespace>Assimalign.Cohesion.Web</RootNamespace>
	</PropertyGroup>
	<ItemGroup>
		<CohesionProjectReference Include="Assimalign.Cohesion.Http" />
	</ItemGroup>
</Project>
